body:
#### Issue details

ObjectMap copy constructor fails as of libgdx 1.7.2 :

``` java
ObjectMap<String, Object> dataCopy = new ObjectMap<String, Object>(data); 
```

See example below.
#### Reproduction steps/code

``` java
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.ObjectMap;

public class ObjectMapCopyCtorBug
{
    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception
    {
        ObjectMap<String, Object> data = new ObjectMap<String, Object>();
        for (int i = 0; i < 17; i++) // above a certain size copy fails 
            data.put("key" + i, i + 0.5f);

        ObjectMap<String, Object> dataCopy = new ObjectMap<String, Object>(data); // copy ctor fails as of libgdx 1.7.2
        for (int i = 0; i < data.size; i++)
        {
            String key = "key" + i;
            Object dataValue = data.get(key);
            Object dataCopyValue = dataCopy.get(key);
            System.out.println(dataValue + " = " + dataCopyValue);
            if (!dataValue.equals(dataCopyValue))
                System.out.println("wrong copy for key " + key);
        }
    }
}
```

